cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper presents a technique for auditing predictive models for subgroup discrimination, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning fairness. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses GANs and optimal transport, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and computer vision, respectively, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the ranking of features, which is a common technique in data science and machine learning, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for attacks on the model, which falls under the category of computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
